body:
This PR adds a new built-in mdedup for detecting duplicates in frames using matching dependencies (like Street 0.95, City 0.90 -> ZIP 1.0). 
@Shafaq-Siddiqi For simplicity, I used Jaccard similarity, but found out that Levenshtein or Jaro distance could also be used, should I also add them? To compute Jaccard similarity between rows (strings) of a vector (nx1) the map with 2 args was added dist = map(Xi, "(x, y) -> UtilFunctions.jaccardSim(x, y)").

I also modified discoverFD built-in by setting diag to 1.
